This paper is about training neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of sparsity in neural networks, which is a topic that is relevant to both cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper presents results on benchmark tasks that involve image classification, which is a common application of deep learning in the field of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in the field of control systems (cs.SY).
